## BOUNDARY (Edge Conditions)

```
⊖ dark_play               .55 | play with transgressive content; tests C2,nonzero_impact
⊖ serious_games           .50 | play instrumentalized for learning/therapy; tests C1
⊖ method_acting           .48 | immersion so deep C3 is strained
⊖ gambling                .45 | real stakes leak through frame; C2 boundary case
⊖ ritual                  .42 | sacred play where frame is metaphysically load-bearing
⊖ virtual_play            .40 | digital/VR spaces strain C3,C5; blurred boundaries
⊖ mandatory_fun           .38 | institutional "play" with penalty for refusal (tests C1)
⊖ bluffing                .35 | playful deception with shared recognition vs lying
⊖ instinctual_play        .32 | animal/human instinctual behaviors; tests C3 limits
⊖ dreaming                .30 | involuntary play; C1 absent, C3 partial
⊖ algorithmic_play        .28 | AI-driven play without clear agency; strains C1
⊖ lying                   .25 | frame exists but is concealed; C4 violation
⊖ pathological_play       .22 | addiction; C1 and C5 fail simultaneously
⊖ audience                .20 | witnesses who validate; optional amplifier (→C5)
```

